intro: Dissochaeta quintuplinervis, commonly known as the five-veined dissochaeta, is a species of flowering plant in the family Rubiaceae. It is characterized by its small, clustered inflorescences and elliptical leaves with five distinct veins. The plant typically grows in tropical and subtropical regions, often in shaded, humid environments. Its flowers are usually white or pale yellow, with four to five petals. The species is of interest to botanists due to its unique venation pattern and ecological adaptability.
